                    <div class='comment-text'>
                        <br />
OK... I believe this is the gist of what I said:<br />
<br />
There is a discrepancy between the coordinates of this submission and the image on the thumbnail (which has now been fixed).<br />
<br />
The coordinates point to the Northwest Ruffner mountain top surface mine, operated by Cardinal Coal Services and covering an area of 1335.69 acres. (The map no longer points to this mine; it is located at <a rel="nofollow" href="http://maps.google.com/maps?q=Yolyn">http://maps.google.com/maps?q=Yolyn</a>,+WV&t=k&ll=37.817107,-81.862221&spn=0.030783,0.086517&t=k)<br />
<br />
The thumbnail displays an image of the Twilight surface mine, operated by Bundy Auger Mining and Independence Coal Company, and covers an area of 3428.57 acres. (The coordinates now correctly match this mine.)<br />
<br />
Figures are from the West Virginia Department of Environmental Protection, <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.wvdep.org/">http://www.wvdep.org/</a><br />
